1. Metanoetic Core (codex/nous/meta.py)

import json, math, statistics
from codex.graph.model import MKG
from telemetry.metrics import METRICS

def evaluate_cognition(window=500):
    nodes=MKG().all()[-window:]
    kinds=[n['kind'] for n in nodes]
    freq={k:kinds.count(k) for k in set(kinds)}
    entropy=-sum((c/sum(freq.values()))*math.log2(c/sum(freq.values())) for c in freq.values())
    balance=round(1/(1+abs(freq.get('inference',0)-freq.get('proposal',0)+1)),3)
    METRICS.event('meta_eval', entropy=round(entropy,3), balance=balance)
    score=(entropy*balance)
    MKG().add('metacognition',{'entropy':entropy,'balance':balance,'score':score})
    return score

This module:

Calculates cognitive entropy (diversity of reasoning nodes).

Measures balance (equilibrium between hypothesis and inference).

Writes â€œmetacognitionâ€ nodes into the MKG.

Reports to telemetry in real time.



